Definition: law) the act of rescinding
Example: the cancellation of a contract and the return of the parties to the positions they would have had if the contract had not been made; recission may be brought about by decree or by mutual consent
Synonyms: verb, communication, rescind, rescission, cancellation, noun, group, law, c, the, act, of, rescinding, a, contract, and, return, parties, to, positions, they, would, have, had, if, not, been, made, may, be, brought, about, by, decree, or, mutual, consent
Category: noun.act
